// src/pages/outdoor/patio-heater-repair/brands/aei.astro
// Wave 5a — AEI / Indeeco patio heater brand page (US commercial heating heritage).
// Indeeco division specializing in commercial infrared heating since 1922.
// Less residential, more commercial: restaurant chain, hotel, warehouse-adjacent outdoor.
// $120 OUTDOOR diagnostic universal. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 #1346255700410.
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/outdoor/patio-heater-repair/brands/aei/";

const title = "AEI / Indeeco Patio Heater Repair LA | Commercial Infrared Specialist — $120 Outdoor";
const description = `AEI / Indeeco commercial infrared patio heater repair across SoCal. Restaurant chain, hotel, warehouse-adjacent outdoor heating. Multi-element bank repair. $120 outdoor diagnostic. ${phone}.`;

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "AEI vs Indeeco. Same company?",
    a: "Yes. Indeeco (Industrial Engineering Equipment Co) is the parent organization, founded in 1922 with a focus on commercial electric heating. AEI is the product line designation for the patio and outdoor commercial infrared heating products specifically. Indeeco's broader portfolio includes industrial process heating, warehouse heating, and commercial space heating. The AEI patio line is positioned as the commercial-tier outdoor infrared product within that broader catalog. We service AEI/Indeeco branded equipment across the residential and commercial range, though the brand is heavily skewed toward commercial installations in LA.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why is AEI less common in residential?",
    a: "AEI/Indeeco is positioned as commercial-tier with larger-format multi-element bank heaters designed for high-throughput restaurant patios, hotel rooftops, and warehouse-adjacent outdoor heating. Residential applications would generally use the smaller-format Bromic, Infratech, Solaira, or Sunpak units. AEI's footprint and BTU output are oversized for typical residential covered patio use; the brand fits restaurant chain, hotel, and commercial venue installations where multi-element coverage is needed. We do service residential AEI installations when present (more common in larger estate properties or commercial-converted residential), though most calls are commercial.",
  },
  {
    q: "Multi-element bank: what fails on these?",
    a: "AEI heaters use bank architecture: multiple heating elements arranged in parallel within the housing. When one element fails, the others continue operating, so the heater still produces heat but at reduced output. Symptom: customer notices reduced heat output, but heater still seems to work. Diagnostic identifies which element(s) failed. Replacement runs $440 to $680 per element bank typical (bank includes element plus housing/reflector subassembly). Sometimes paired with contactor or relay service if the bank wiring is at fault rather than the elements themselves.",
  },
  {
    q: "Contactor or relay issues are common?",
    a: "Yes. Commercial AEI installations use contactors and relays rated for repeated cycle service (8 to 14 hours daily, multi-cycle per day). Year 8 to 12 typical for contactor wear; relays sometimes earlier (year 6 to 9) depending on switching frequency. Replacement runs $340 to $540 typical. Often paired with control panel module service if the controller is sending intermittent signals.",
  },
  {
    q: "Building automation integration. Do you handle that?",
    a: "We service the AEI hardware side: heating elements, contactors, relays, control panel modules, wiring terminations. Building automation integration (BACnet, Modbus, low-voltage controller programming, scheduling logic) is low-voltage integrator trade. We work with several LA-area integrators and can refer if the issue is automation-side rather than heater hardware. We diagnose to identify which side is the cause; we don't pretend to handle integrator work we're not licensed for.",
  },
  {
    q: "Mounting bracket structural fatigue?",
    a: "AEI/Indeeco commercial heaters are heavier than residential brands (multi-element bank weight, larger housing). Year 10+ commercial duty installations sometimes show mounting bracket structural fatigue, especially on installations that weren't originally specified for the unit weight (older retrofit installs). Bracket inspection is part of our diagnostic on year 8+ AEI calls; replacement bracket plus structural reinforcement runs $440 to $680 typical, sometimes paired with engineer assessment for structural integrity verification.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. Indeeco / AEI component warranties (heating element bank, contactor, relay, control panel module) where applicable processed separately. BHGS #A49573, BBB A+ accredited, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410.",
  },
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair", "url": canonical, "telephone": phone, "priceRange": "$$$",
    "openingHoursSpecification": [{ "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday"], "opens": "08:00", "closes": "20:00" }],
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" },
    ],
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "AEI Patio Heater Repair", "name": "AEI / Indeeco Commercial Infrared Patio Heater Repair Service", "url": canonical,
    "description": "AEI / Indeeco commercial infrared patio heater repair across all five SoCal counties. Multi-element bank heaters, commercial-tier electric infrared, restaurant chain installations, hotel patios and rooftops, warehouse-adjacent outdoor heating. Service: element bank failures (one of multi-element bank fails while others continue, year 6-9 commercial), contactor and relay replacement (year 8-12 typical), control panel module service, wiring termination corrosion at commercial junction box (year 10+), mounting bracket structural fatigue, thermostat and sensor drift on building automation integrations. Less common in residential; primary use commercial. $120 outdoor diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410.",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" },
    ],
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceRange": "$120-$1500", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "120.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Outdoor diagnostic fee, applied toward repair. No emergency surcharge." } },
    "brand": { "@id": canonical + "#brand" },
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Brand", "@id": canonical + "#brand",
    "name": "AEI / Indeeco",
    "url": "https://www.indeeco.com/",
    "description": "Indeeco (Industrial Engineering Equipment Co) is an American commercial electric heating manufacturer founded in 1922. The AEI product line designation covers the patio and outdoor commercial infrared heating products within Indeeco's broader catalog. Commercial-tier focus: restaurant chain installations, hotel patios and rooftops, warehouse-adjacent outdoor heating. Multi-element bank architecture with parallel heating elements for high-throughput coverage. Less common in residential than Bromic, Infratech, Solaira, or Sunpak; primary market is commercial.",
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Outdoor", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/outdoor/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Patio Heater Repair", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/outdoor/patio-heater-repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "AEI / Indeeco", "item": canonical },
    ],
  },
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<ServiceHero
  eyebrow="AEI / Indeeco · Commercial Infrared Specialist · Restaurant + Hotel + Warehouse"
  title="AEI / Indeeco Patio Heater Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle={`Commercial-tier multi-element infrared bank heaters. Restaurant chain, hotel patios, warehouse-adjacent outdoor. $120 outdoor diagnostic, waived with repair. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="AEI / Indeeco Commercial Patio Heater Repair"
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">AEI / Indeeco service</p>
    <h2>Commercial infrared specialist. Multi-element bank heaters for restaurant chain, hotel, and warehouse-adjacent installations.</h2>

    <p>Indeeco (Industrial Engineering Equipment Co) is the American commercial electric heating manufacturer founded in 1922. The AEI product line covers the patio and outdoor commercial infrared heating products within Indeeco's broader catalog (which also includes industrial process heating and commercial space heating). Commercial-tier positioning: AEI heaters are larger-format with multi-element bank architecture designed for high-throughput restaurant patios, hotel rooftops, and warehouse-adjacent outdoor heating coverage. Less common in residential than smaller-format brands; primary market is commercial.</p>

    <p>Common LA installations: restaurant chain outdoor patios with multi-unit deployment, hotel patios and rooftops needing high-coverage outdoor heating, warehouse-adjacent commercial venues, and occasional larger-estate residential installations where commercial-tier output is needed.</p>

    <p>We service the AEI / Indeeco lineup across LA County, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Multi-element bank infrared heaters, commercial-grade contactor and relay service, control panel module replacement, building automation integration coordination (we handle hardware; integrator partner handles automation programming).</p>

    <p>$120 outdoor diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/outdoor/patio-heater-repair/">patio heater repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Lineup and what fails</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">AEI / Indeeco architecture and common service items.</h2>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Multi-element bank architecture</h3>
    <p>AEI heaters use parallel-element bank design: multiple heating elements arranged in parallel within a single housing. When one element fails, the others continue operating, so the heater still produces heat but at reduced output. This is fundamentally different from residential single-element brands (Bromic Tungsten, Infratech, Solaira). Diagnostic on AEI bank heaters identifies which specific element(s) in the bank failed; replacement is per-element rather than full unit.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Commercial-grade switching components</h3>
    <p>Contactors and relays in AEI commercial installations are rated for repeated cycle service (8 to 14 hours daily, multi-cycle per day). These wear at year 6 to 12 depending on switching frequency. Building automation integration (BACnet, Modbus) sometimes adds intermediate relays in the control path; service includes verifying the entire switching chain.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Common service items</h3>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Element bank failures (year 6-9 commercial).</strong> One element of multi-element bank fails; others continue. $440-680 per element bank.</li>
      <li><strong>Contactor wear (year 8-12).</strong> $340-540 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Relay failure (year 6-9 high-switching-frequency installs).</strong> $260-440.</li>
      <li><strong>Control panel module (year 6-9).</strong> $340-540.</li>
      <li><strong>Wiring termination corrosion at commercial junction box (year 10+).</strong> $200-340 service.</li>
      <li><strong>Mounting bracket structural fatigue (year 10+ heavy commercial duty).</strong> $440-680, sometimes paired with engineer assessment.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermostat / sensor drift on building automation.</strong> $200-340, plus integrator coordination if automation-side issue.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top AEI / Indeeco repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Element bank failure (year 6-9 commercial, #1 AEI service item).</strong> One element of multi-element bank fails. $440-680 per bank.</li>
      <li><strong>Contactor wear (year 8-12).</strong> $340-540.</li>
      <li><strong>Control panel module (year 6-9).</strong> $340-540.</li>
      <li><strong>Relay failure (year 6-9 high-frequency switching).</strong> $260-440.</li>
      <li><strong>Wiring termination corrosion (year 10+).</strong> $200-340.</li>
      <li><strong>Mounting bracket structural fatigue (year 10+).</strong> $440-680.</li>
