</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>West Hollywood restaurant chain patio, AEI 6-element bank heater (commercial), 7 years old</h3>
        <p>Customer reported reduced output but unit still running. Diagnosed: 2 of 6 elements in bank failed (year 7 commercial duty). Replaced both element banks, tested remaining 4 (still serviceable). Total: $120 plus $1,000 (2 banks × $500) plus $300 install = $1,420.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marina del Rey hotel rooftop, AEI commercial 4-unit installation, 9 years old</h3>
        <p>Two units stopped running entirely. Diagnostic identified contactor failure on one (year 9 commercial wear) and main control panel module on the other (different fault, same age). Replaced contactor, replaced control panel module. Total: $120 plus $440 contactor plus $440 control module plus $300 install = $1,300.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pasadena warehouse-adjacent commercial venue, AEI bank heater (commercial), 11 years old</h3>
        <p>Multi-component cumulative service: contactor wear, relay failure, mounting bracket showing structural fatigue. Replaced contactor and relay, installed reinforced mounting bracket per engineer assessment. Total: $120 plus $440 contactor plus $360 relay plus $580 bracket plus install = $1,800. Year 11 commercial unit good for another 5+ years with this service.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills estate residential, AEI commercial bank (year 8, residential duty)</h3>
        <p>Year 8 residential installation (lower duty cycle than commercial). Single element bank failure. Less compressed timeline than commercial because residential 50-200 hr/yr duty puts less stress. Replaced one element bank. Total: $120 plus $500 bank plus $200 install = $820. Estate property, large residential covered patio coverage.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

