    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for AEI / Indeeco, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>AEI / Indeeco multi-element bank infrared heaters</li>
      <li>Commercial-grade contactor and relay service</li>
      <li>Control panel module replacement</li>
      <li>Wiring termination corrosion at commercial junction box</li>
      <li>Mounting bracket structural assessment and replacement</li>
      <li>Thermostat and sensor drift on standalone control</li>
      <li>Hardware-side coordination with building automation integrators</li>
      <li>Multi-unit restaurant and hotel installations</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new AEI / Indeeco installation (commercial electrical rough-in is electrician trade with appropriate amperage rating; ceiling structural mounting requires engineer involvement on commercial-load installations); building automation programming (BACnet, Modbus, custom scheduling logic — low-voltage integrator trade); structural engineering for mounting load assessment (engineer trade, we coordinate when needed); high-voltage panel work for amperage upgrades (electrician with appropriate license tier).</p>
